review_blob: Ive had this beer several times and its always so amazing. This is a bottle I had for about 8 months now. It pours black and creamy with some head. Aroma is molasses and toasted malt. Flavor is bitter chocolate and hops. Palate is full bodied and creamy with a bitter hops finish. This is one of my favorite stouts.

Finally found some of this in bottles. Pours a liquidy, dark color with little head. Aroma is of coffee and malt. Taste is lots of sweet coffee, malt and slight bitterness. Very thin in the palate. Overall an awesome beer.
beer_name: Cigar City Cubano-Style Espresso Brown Ale

review_blob: From a bottle. Pours black with hardly any carbonation. Aroma is chocolate and honey. Taste is sweet caramel with a bit of bitterness from the hops. Medium body with a bitter finish. I dont know if there was something off with this bottle, but it was much better when I had it on tap. I still prefer the Or over this one.

From a bottle. Pours black with little head and lots of lingering lacing. Aroma is heavy on hops and cedar with some chocolate. Taste is sweet and hoppy with bitterness from the cedar. Palate is a nice mouthful feel with a bitter ending. Im very pleased with how this beer turned out.

I brought a bottle of this back from Brazil and finally got around to drinking it. Pours a cloudy dark amber color. Aroma is citrus, some fruit and malt. Taste is slightly sweet and malty with some hop bitterness. Light and thin with some ending sweetness. I was not super impressed with this one.

I have had this beer several times, but this bottle I had saved for a little over a year. It pours pitch black with a very thick and creamy head with lots of sticky lacing. Aroma is toasted malt and some coffee. Taste is oak, toasted malt, coffee and chocolate. Palate is medium body, creamy and slightly dry. Very little alcohol is noticed in the finish. This bottle has been, by far the best one so far.
beer_name: Great Divide Yeti Imperial Stout - Oak Aged

review_blob: On tap. Pours a bright orange. Aroma is spices and brown suggar. Taste is sweet and fruity. Nice carbonation and sticky on the palate. Though not one of my favirite styles, this is a decent beer.

From a bottle. Pours a very dark color with little head and little lacing. Carbonation seems very low. Aroma is very little chocolate and toasted malts. Taste is sweet and malty. Medium body with a bitter, slightly sweet finish.
From a bottle. Pours a nice, bright copper color with very little head and lacing. Aroma is sweet, earth/floral hops and malt. Taste is very fresh hops. Thin mouth feel with a slightly sweet finish.
beer_name: Terrapin So Fresh & So Green Green 2010 (Amarillo)

review_blob: From a bottle, pours black with very little head. Aroma is mostly toasted malts with the licorice being more subtle. Taste is bitter chocolate with very little sweetness. Medium body, more on the thin side for this style. Overall this is a very good stout.

Pours a dark redish brown color with minimal head. Lots of molasses on the nose with some caramel and some plum. Taste is tangy sweet, dark fruit and malt. Palate is medium bodied with mild carbonation and sweet finish.

From a bottle, even after being in the fridge for several days it started foaming out of the bottle shortly after opening it. Pours a hazy golden yellow with lots of head. Aroma is sour, malt, yeast and citrus hops. Taste is sour and bitter with a bit of a malt presence. Palate is dry with a nice amount of carbonation and a dry finish.

From a bottle thanks to Jay (fear025). Pours a dark redish brown with medium head and a good amount of lacing. Aroma is malty, caramel and brown sugar. Flavor is sweet and malty. Medium bodied with a smooth finish.

From a bottle thanks to Jay (fear025). Pours very dark with very little carbonation/head and minimal lacing. Aroma is sweet, molasses, brown sugar and malt. Flavor is mostly sweet malts with some caramel and a bit of bitter. Full bodied and chewy with a bitter finish.

From a bottle, big thanks to Jay (fear025). Pours a dark red with little head and lots of lacing. Aroma is bitter hops and alcohol. Taste is pretty bitter hops with some citrus. Palate is thin with a lingering bitter finish. I was looking forward to this one and had my expectations set high. Though it is very good, it left me expecting more.

I bought a single bottle of this from a local beer store. It pours dark with little head. Aroma caramel and toffee. Taste is sweet and malty. Palate is full body with a decent amount of carbonation and a slight bitter finish. Very nice!
Pours very dark with little head/carbonation. Smells very sweet with caramel, sugar, oak and malt. Taste of caramel and wood. Palate is thick, creamy and amazing. Wow, fantastic beer.

From a bottle, thanks to Jay (fear025). Pours a rich, clear dark orange color, with a decent amount of head. Aroma is floral hops and citrus, very fresh. Flavor is fresh hops and some citrus. Palate is medium and slightly oily. Overall amazing imperial IPA.

I opened a bottle a got at the brewery several months ago. It was much different than when I had it on tap. Poured a dark copper with medium head. Smells like a cigar box. Tastes like a lambic, but more fruity. Very good. Possibly one of my favorite from CCB.

From a bottle thanks to Jay (fear025). Very light gold, clear with minimal head and little lacing. Aroma is light floral hops and citrus. Tastes light and slightly bitter. Very nice light palate, with a bit of lingering bitterness at the end. Very nice indeed.
beer_name: New Glarus Moon Man No Coast Pale Ale

review_blob: From a tap. Pours a rich coper with little head and some lacing. Aroma is floral hops. Flavor is bitter hops and a tiny bit of malt. Palete is thin and slightly oily. Overall a great beer.

From a bottle a friend brought over. Pours a dark, clear golden copper with very little head and no lacing. Smells like sweet pumpkin pie, no joke. Taste is sweet spices and pumpkin. Very thin palate. This is a very interesting pumpkin ale. Not at all what I would expect, but not bad by any means.
beer_name: Southern Tier Coles 75th Anniversary Pumpkin IPA

review_blob: Had this from a bottle. Poured a huge head, cloudy light yellow color. Aroma is lost of yeast and hops. Taste yeast and hops, very  bitter. Palate is fizzy and dry. Overall a pretty good farmhouse ale.

From a bottle. Dark brown with lots of head. Aroma is caramel, yeast and some berries. Flavor is heavy in blackberries, cherries, malt and brown sugar. Medium bodied with a smooth finish and slightly tangy/sweet aftertaste. Very good!

Pours a slightly cloudy orange color with little head that quickly subsides leaving behind little lacing. Aroma is hops, citrus and caramel. Flavor is hoppy and malty, probably slightly more malty than your average IPA. Nice hops in the end for pretty smooth finish. Overall a decent IPA.
beer_name: Cigar City Jai Alai India Pale Ale

review_blob: From a bottle, pours a golden amber. Cloudy with a nice amount of head leaving behind lots of lacing. Aroma is citrus, hops and a bit of malt. Flavor is hoppy/bitter and sweet with a slightly bitter finish. Palate is thin to medium body. Overall this is a great double IPA. I would put this in the top 5 of my favorit IPAs.

Pours a very dark brown with overflowing and lingering head that produces a log of lacing. Aroma is of caramel, cereal and malts. Tastes sweet and malty. Palate is medium body with a creamy texture and a long finish. Ive had this beer several times and, although it is well made it is not one of my favorites and I cant usually have more than 1.

From a bottle. Pours a clear light amber color with little head that subsides very quickly leaving behind lacing on the glass. Aroma is heavy of citrus and hops. Taste is bitter with a hint of sweetness at the end. Palate is light, thin and fizzy with a slightly bitter ending. The 90 minute is one of my favorite session IPAs with the 60 minute being a very close second. This is a great beer for the Florida heat.

From a bottle. Pours a very dark brown with lingering medium head that produces lacing. The aroma is mostly coffee, chocolate and some malt. Taste of dark bitter chocolate and coffee. Palate is smooth, medium body with a lingering finish. Overall this is a great beer.
beer_name: Cigar City Jos Mart American Porter

review_blob: Pours a clear orange with medium head. Aroma is sweet, malty and a little hops. Tastes slightly sweet and bitter. Creamy texture with a slightly oaky, sweet finish. Very nice.
Pours a dark amber color with a thin, lasting head. Aroma is of dark berries and vinegar. Taste is a bit acetic and fizzy with some oak notes. Overall a great sour ale.
Dark brown with little to no head. Aroma is gingerish with some caramel. Taste is bitter/acetic with spices. Palate is thin and watery. Decent overall, but not one of my favorites.

From a bottle. Pours a golden amber color. Clear with little head. Aroma is very hoppy with some grapefruit. Flavor is very well balanced, lots of hops and some citrus. Palate is a little dry. Overall an excellent IPA.
Pours a clear yellow with medium head. Light hop and malt aromas. Light on the palate with a bit of bitterness.

Im very happy to have received this on a trade. RR makes some amazing beers and this one is no exception. It pours a bright golder, slightly cloudy with very little head. Aroma is hoppy, floral and very fresh. Flavor is slightly dry and hoppy, but not overwhelming with a smooth finish.
Pours a dark cherry color with little head. Aroma is sour with hints of cherry. Flavor is tart, but not acidic. Very good overall.
